{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h1 id=\"gatsby-cli\"><a href=\"#gatsby-cli\" aria-label=\"gatsby cli permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>gatsby-cli</h1>\n<p>The Gatsby command line interface (CLI). It is used to perform common functionality, such as creating a Gatsby application based on a starter, spinning up a hot-reloading local development server, and more!</p>\n<h2 id=\"note-on-globally-installed-executables\"><a href=\"#note-on-globally-installed-executables\" aria-label=\"note on globally installed executables permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Note on globally installed executables</h2>\n<p>The Gatsby CLI (<code class=\"language-text\">gatsby-cli</code>) is packaged as an executable that can be used globally—in fact, this was previously how we recommended using the CLI.</p>\n<p>However, global installs of the Gatsby CLI can sometimes lead to subtle bugs in behavior and functionality if the version of the globally installed executable does not match the version of Gatsby in your application. To avoid this, we highly recommend using the <code class=\"language-text\">package.json</code> script variant of these commands, typically exposed <em>for you</em> with most starters.</p>\n<p>For example, if we want to make the <a href=\"#develop\"><code class=\"language-text\">gatsby develop</code></a> command available in our application, we would open up <code class=\"language-text\">package.json</code> and add a script like so:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"json:title\"><pre class=\"language-json:title\"><code class=\"language-json:title\">{\n  &quot;scripts&quot;: {\n    &quot;develop&quot;: &quot;gatsby develop&quot;\n  }\n}</code></pre></div>\n<p>We can now use the <code class=\"language-text\">develop</code> script tied to our app’s version of Gatsby, rather than a globally installed version. This script can be invoked by using the name of the script, e.g. <code class=\"language-text\">npm run develop</code> in this case. Feel free to <a href=\"https://docs.npmjs.com/misc/scripts\">read more about NPM scripts</a> if you’re interested!</p>\n<h2 id=\"how-to-use\"><a href=\"#how-to-use\" aria-label=\"how to use permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>How to use</h2>\n<p>Rather than installing the Gatsby CLI tool locally you can run it using <a href=\"https://www.npmjs.com/package/npx\">npx</a></p>\n<p>To see the commands available to run <code class=\"language-text\">npx gatsby --help</code>.</p>\n<h2 id=\"commands\"><a href=\"#commands\" aria-label=\"commands permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Commands</h2>\n<h3 id=\"new\"><a href=\"#new\" aria-label=\"new permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a><code class=\"language-text\">new</code></h3>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">npx gatsby new gatsby-site</code></p>\n<p>See the <a href=\"https://www.gatsbyjs.org/docs/gatsby-starters/\">Gatsby starters docs</a>\nfor more.</p>\n<h3 id=\"develop\"><a href=\"#develop\" aria-label=\"develop permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a><code class=\"language-text\">develop</code></h3>\n<p>At the root of a Gatsby site run <code class=\"language-text\">gatsby develop</code> to start the Gatsby\ndevelopment server.</p>\n<h4 id=\"options\"><a href=\"#options\" aria-label=\"options permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Options</h4>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th align=\"center\">Option</th>\n<th>Description</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"center\"><code class=\"language-text\">-H</code>, <code class=\"language-text\">--host</code></td>\n<td>Set host. Defaults to localhost</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"center\"><code class=\"language-text\">-p</code>, <code class=\"language-text\">--port</code></td>\n<td>Set port. Defaults to 8000</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"center\"><code class=\"language-text\">-o</code>, <code class=\"language-text\">--open</code></td>\n<td>Open the site in your (default) browser for you</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"center\"><code class=\"language-text\">-S</code>, <code class=\"language-text\">--https</code></td>\n<td>Use HTTPS</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Follow the <a href=\"https://www.gatsbyjs.org/docs/local-https/\">Local HTTPS guide</a>\nto find out how you can set up an HTTPS development server using Gatsby.</p>\n<h3 id=\"build\"><a href=\"#build\" aria-label=\"build permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a><code class=\"language-text\">build</code></h3>\n<p>At the root of a Gatsby site use <code class=\"language-text\">gatsby build</code> to do a production build of a\nsite.</p>\n<h4 id=\"options-1\"><a href=\"#options-1\" aria-label=\"options 1 permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Options</h4>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th align=\"center\">Option</th>\n<th>Description</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"center\"><code class=\"language-text\">--prefix-paths</code></td>\n<td>Build site with link paths prefixed (set pathPrefix in your config)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"center\"><code class=\"language-text\">--no-uglify</code></td>\n<td>Build site without uglifying JS bundles (for debugging)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"center\"><code class=\"language-text\">--open-tracing-config-file</code></td>\n<td>Tracer configuration file (open tracing compatible). See <a href=\"https://www.gatsbyjs.org/docs/performance-tracing/\">https://www.gatsbyjs.org/docs/performance-tracing/</a></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h3 id=\"serve\"><a href=\"#serve\" aria-label=\"serve permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Serve</h3>\n<p>At the root of a Gatsby site use <code class=\"language-text\">gatsby serve</code> to serve the production build of\nthe site for testing.</p>\n<h4 id=\"options-2\"><a href=\"#options-2\" aria-label=\"options 2 permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Options</h4>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th align=\"center\">Option</th>\n<th>Description</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"center\"><code class=\"language-text\">-H</code>, <code class=\"language-text\">--host</code></td>\n<td>Set host. Defaults to localhost</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"center\"><code class=\"language-text\">-p</code>, <code class=\"language-text\">--port</code></td>\n<td>Set port. Defaults to 8000</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"center\"><code class=\"language-text\">-o</code>, <code class=\"language-text\">--open</code></td>\n<td>Open the site in your (default) browser for you</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"center\"><code class=\"language-text\">--prefix-paths</code></td>\n<td>Serve site with link paths prefixed (if built with pathPrefix in your gatsby-config.js).</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h3 id=\"info\"><a href=\"#info\" aria-label=\"info permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Info</h3>\n<p>At the root of a Gatsby site run <code class=\"language-text\">npx gatsby info</code> to get helpful environment information which will be required when reporting a bug.</p>\n<h4 id=\"options-3\"><a href=\"#options-3\" aria-label=\"options 3 permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Options</h4>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th align=\"center\">Option</th>\n<th>Description</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"center\"><code class=\"language-text\">-C</code>, <code class=\"language-text\">--clipboard</code></td>\n<td>Automagically copy environment information to clipboard</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h3 id=\"repl\"><a href=\"#repl\" aria-label=\"repl permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Repl</h3>\n<p>Get a node repl with context of Gatsby environment</p>\n<!-- TODO: add repl documentation link when ready -->","excerpt":"gatsby-cli The Gatsby command line interface (CLI). It is used to perform common functionality, such as creating a Gatsby application based…","timeToRead":3,"fields":{"title":"gatsby-cli"},"parent":{"__typename":"File","relativePath":"gatsby-cli/README.md"}},"npmPackage":null},"pageContext":{"slug":"/packages/gatsby-cli/"}}